subject: Tennis
lead_paragraph: Dinara Safina will overtake Serena Williams for the No. 1 ranking later this month. The WTA Tour said Safina would rise to No. 1 for the first time in her career in the April 20 rankings. Safina is the younger sister of the former men’s No. 1 Marat Safin. They are the first brother and sister to be No. 1. Safina was the runner-up at the 2008 French Open to Ana Ivanovic and at the 2009 Australian Open to Williams.
